 :tx/rationale "C9-P5-REVISION: Every braid output is a steering event on the LLM latent space manifold. A flat observation list sorted by timestamp is the WORST possible steering — it gives the agent 226 lines to scan with no structure. The observe subcommands must be STEERING-OPTIMIZED: (1) braid observe list should GROUP by concept cluster, annotate each group with member count + confidence range + most-surprising member. Top 5 clusters by default. This steers the agent toward the knowledge STRUCTURE, not just content. (2) braid observe search PATTERN should RANK results by: relevance to search term (0.4) + structural importance via link count from C9-P2 (0.3) + confidence (0.2) + recency (0.1). Not flat substring matching. This steers the agent toward the most important matching observations, not just any match. (3) braid observe show ENTITY should include: full body, confidence, category, concept membership, INCOMING links (what depends on this), OUTGOING links (what this depends on), creation timestamp, agent source. This steers the agent to understand the observation in its graph context. (4) braid observe recent N should show the N most recent WITH their concept assignment, so the agent sees what themes emerged recently. The key insight from the earlier session: braid is not a knowledge store, it is a navigation system for a pre-existing knowledge manifold. The observe subcommands must NAVIGATE, not just LIST."
